ZPL is a markup language so there is no logic you can really add to it.  Logic has to be done in the code that is sending the ZPL. An example in Javascript would look something like:

    var listData = &quot;Surimi Salad, Kanikama, Cream cheeseSurimi Salad, Kanikama, Cream cheese&quot;;
    var fontwidth = 20;
    var width = 300;
    var lines = 3;
    if (((listData.length * fontwidth)/width) &gt; lines)
        fontwidth = fontwidth - 5;
    var zpl = &quot;^XA^A0N,&quot; + fontwidth + &quot;,&quot; + fontwidth + &quot;^FB&quot; + width + &quot;,&quot; + lines + &quot;,0,C^FD&quot; + listData + &quot;^FS^XZ&quot;;

It won&#39;t be exact as most fonts are variable width, but it will get you closer to a fit.

